# Only public/ (the built Flutter web output) and api/ (the serverless
# proxy) need to reach Vercel. Everything else here is local Flutter/Dart
# tooling state or native-platform build output -- .gitignore covers these
# too, but Vercel's own upload step doesn't reliably honor it (confirmed:
# a deploy attempt uploaded 1.5GB, matching build/app + .dart_tool, and
# failed on Vercel's 100MB per-file limit), so this file makes the
# exclusion explicit rather than inferred.
build/
.dart_tool/
android/
ios/
web/
test/
integration_test/
docs/
.superpowers/
node_modules/
coverage/
*.iml
